Yeah, this set of ingredients
is quite common, I'd say.

00:20:17.370 --> 00:20:20.870
Recipes that I love
from the book--

00:20:20.870 --> 00:20:23.070
so it's the things that
I cook quite often,

00:20:23.070 --> 00:20:28.710
is there is a pasta dish
with harissa, olive, capers.

00:20:28.710 --> 00:20:37.520
And it's a North African
inspired set of ingredients.

00:20:37.520 --> 00:20:40.530
And so I took the liberty
to add some yogurt when

00:20:40.530 --> 00:20:42.330
I serve it, which
is not very Italian,

00:20:42.330 --> 00:20:45.450
and pasta is considered
to be an Italian thing.

00:20:45.450 --> 00:20:48.210
But the connections between
North Africa and Southern Italy

00:20:48.210 --> 00:20:49.950
are really very,
very evident when

00:20:49.950 --> 00:20:53.370
you go to places like Sicily
or Sardinia or southern Italy.

00:20:53.370 --> 00:20:58.260
So it is a recipe that is
a hybrid of those two food

00:20:58.260 --> 00:20:59.440
cultures.

00:20:59.440 --> 00:21:02.070
And I make it.

00:21:02.070 --> 00:21:07.029
There's a really good brand
of rose harissa from Belazu.

00:21:07.029 --> 00:21:09.570
That's a really good brand, and
you find them in supermarkets

00:21:09.570 --> 00:21:10.560
now.

00:21:10.560 --> 00:21:13.380
And it really doesn't
entail much more

00:21:13.380 --> 00:21:16.320
than getting that and some
tomatoes and, like I said,

00:21:16.320 --> 00:21:17.580
capers, olives.

00:21:17.580 --> 00:21:20.430
And it just creates the
most incredible pasta.

00:21:20.430 --> 00:21:23.550
And you could put
it on the table

00:21:23.550 --> 00:21:25.560
within the time it
takes to cook the pasta,

00:21:25.560 --> 00:21:27.360
or just a little bit
longer than that.

00:21:27.360 --> 00:21:28.962
So that's a favorite.

